<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 22 at 4:14PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Phillips,
northeastern Petroleum and west central Garfield Counties through 515
PM MDT...
At 414 PM MDT, local law enforcement reported a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Crooked Creek Rec Area, or 26 miles northeast of
Winnett, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Law enforcement.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Crooked Creek Rec Area.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
